that, because it's 2 equations

01:09:13.886 --> 01:09:15.069
and 2 unknowns.
 

01:09:15.069 --> 01:09:15.970
I'm repeating myself.
 

01:09:15.970 --> 01:09:18.720
You even know what
X_L is without writing

01:09:18.720 --> 01:09:22.077
down the equations,
because the gap has to be--one

01:09:22.077 --> 01:09:23.197
thing,
there's no risk,

01:09:23.197 --> 01:09:24.899
and the other thing,
there's a big risk.

01:09:24.899 --> 01:09:29.380
So the only risk in the payoff
has to come from the long bond.

01:09:29.380 --> 01:09:31.935
So that gap of 38,
if you take 7 thirty-eighths of

01:09:31.935 --> 01:09:34.649
that, you're going to get the
gap to go down to 7.

01:09:34.649 --> 01:09:37.170
So the X_L's going to
turn out to be 7 thirty-eighths.

01:09:37.170 --> 01:09:39.939
X_S you have to solve
by algebra.

01:09:39.939 --> 01:09:42.631
So you know how much that
X_L is and what the

01:09:42.631 --> 01:09:43.578
X_S is.
 

01:09:43.578 --> 01:09:45.791
That's what you hold,
that combination of

01:09:45.791 --> 01:09:48.943
X_L and X_S,
you hold here and you get

01:09:48.943 --> 01:09:50.270
exactly the payoffs.
 

01:09:50.270 --> 01:09:54.298
And then the final step is to
notice that you can exactly

01:09:54.298 --> 01:09:56.529
afford it with 98.84 dollars.
 

01:09:56.529 --> 01:09:58.408
How do you know that you can
afford it?

01:09:58.408 --> 01:10:06.520
Because what you want is 100.6
and 107.11 and that costs 98.84.

01:10:06.520 --> 01:10:14.731
You're buying two things
together whose payoffs together

01:10:14.731 --> 01:10:17.420
are worth 98.84.
 

01:10:17.420 --> 01:10:21.797
So therefore the cost of the
two things separately have to be

01:10:21.797 --> 01:10:22.819
worth 98.84.
 

01:10:22.819 --> 01:10:25.597
So it will turn out when you
solve for X_L and

01:10:25.597 --> 01:10:27.569
X_S,
you'll exactly be able to

01:10:27.569 --> 01:10:29.538
afford it with this amount of
cash.

01:10:29.538 --> 01:10:33.393
So you can just do that going
forward all the time,

01:10:33.393 --> 01:10:36.399
constantly re-hedging your
portfolio.

01:10:36.399 --> 01:10:38.710
So that's the essence of
dynamic hedging.

01:10:38.710 --> 01:10:42.533
It's a very beautiful idea
which I probably haven't

01:10:42.533 --> 01:10:46.944
explained in the optimal way,
but the point is that,

01:10:46.944 --> 01:10:50.250
to summarize the whole thing
again,

01:10:50.250 --> 01:10:57.590
you know something about a
bond, but you're subject to more

01:10:57.590 --> 01:11:01.260
risk besides what you know.
 

01:11:01.260 --> 01:11:04.703
You hedge out the extra risk,
still relying on yourself to be

01:11:04.703 --> 01:11:06.310
right about what you know.
 

01:11:06.310 --> 01:11:08.880
You relied on your being right
about the prepayments.

01:11:08.880 --> 01:11:11.569
You don't know anything about
the future interest rates.

01:11:11.569 --> 01:11:14.264
But there's another guy like
the trader in the World Series,

01:11:14.264 --> 01:11:17.003
the broker in the World Series,
who's willing to make bets on

01:11:17.003 --> 01:11:18.420
the interest rate with you.
 

01:11:18.420 --> 01:11:22.140
Or to say the same thing,
who's been calculating the

01:11:22.140 --> 01:11:25.641
values of the bonds,
the short and the long bond,

01:11:25.641 --> 01:11:29.288
as if he was making bets on the
interest rate.

01:11:29.288 --> 01:11:33.233
He's calculated at the same
50/50 odds, discounting by the

01:11:33.233 --> 01:11:34.340
interest rate.
 

01:11:34.340 --> 01:11:37.320
So because there are all these
guys on the market who are

01:11:37.320 --> 01:11:39.609
willing to make these game by
game bets,

01:11:39.609 --> 01:11:42.341
either directly--I'm almost
done--they either make the game

01:11:42.341 --> 01:11:45.213
by game bets and the interest
rate directly in the derivatives

01:11:45.213 --> 01:11:47.585
market,
or what's equivalent to that,

01:11:47.585 --> 01:11:51.194
they've used that calculus to
figure out the value of these

01:11:51.194 --> 01:11:52.689
long and short bonds.
 

01:11:52.689 --> 01:11:54.654
So by trading through the long
and short bonds,

01:11:54.654 --> 01:11:56.960
you're effectively doing the
same interest rate bet.

01:11:56.960 --> 01:11:59.301
So either way,
by trading through the two

01:11:59.301 --> 01:12:00.912
bonds,
or trading directly in the

01:12:00.912 --> 01:12:03.905
interest rate derivative market,
you're able to buy,

01:12:03.905 --> 01:12:05.979
by going game at a time.
 

01:12:05.979 --> 01:12:08.301
Year by year,
you're able to buy all the cash

01:12:08.301 --> 01:12:10.886
flows of your mortgage,
the cash flows that you're

01:12:10.886 --> 01:12:12.680
predicting it's going to have.
 

01:12:12.680 --> 01:12:15.447
And therefore,
you can make the profit for

01:12:15.447 --> 01:12:15.920
sure.
 

01:12:15.920 --> 01:12:19.435
It's predicting something,
being confident in your

01:12:19.435 --> 01:12:21.829
prediction,
then being able to buy what

01:12:21.829 --> 01:12:25.076
you've predicted the cash flows
are for a smaller price than you

01:12:25.076 --> 01:12:26.569
can sell the security for.
 

01:12:26.569 --> 01:12:28.869
That's how you locked in your
profit.

